cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.ME 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the limitations of common rigid-body contact models used in robotics and proposes data-driven models to overcome these limitations. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses data-driven models to improve the performance of rigid-body contact models. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possibility as the paper may use vision-based sensors to collect the empirical planar impact data-set. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possibility as the paper discusses the use of models in control systems. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with rigid-body contact models in mechanical systems.
